data.description: Thoroughly Upgraded Craftsman Perfect for Entertaining. Expansive open living/dining area with original woodwork, box-beam ceilings and hardwood floors showcase its 1928 Heritage. Home boasts new central AC/furnace, updated kitchen, marble counters, modern baths, new wiring and roof. Large windows invite plenty of sunlight throughout. Working fireplace, built-in cabinets, wainscoting and plate rails have been lovingly maintained. Spacious master suite has French doors leading to a bonus room & bath.
data.whatILove: The large open living space invites you in.  The built- in cabinets in the large dining area adds that craftsman charm.  The woodburning fireplace in the living room also adds to the warmth and beauty of the home.  Lastly, the abundance of windows adds a ton of natural light.  This home is truly a rare jewel in a wonderful neighborhood.
